ce and visions of a scientific Japan. The contested, complex political endeavor of talking about and promoting science produced what the author calls "scientific nationalism," a powerful current of nationalism that has been overlooked by scholars of Japan, nationalism, and modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aImperialism and sciencexHistoryx20th centuryxJapan. 0aImperialism and sciencezJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aNationalism and sciencexHistoryx20th centuryxJapan. 0aNationalism and sciencezJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aReligion and sciencexHistoryx20th centuryxJapan. 0aReligion and sciencezJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aScience and statexHistoryx20th centuryxJapan. 0aScience and statezJapanxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Japan.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476984640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804769846423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804769846.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles